<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-08-18T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-08-18T07:00:00-05:00" n="866" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d866">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">667.003/139: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-08-18T15:00:00+03:00"><hi rend="italic">August 18,
                                        1921—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 19—6:13
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>232. Urgently request instructions concerning taxation plan set forth in
                            my 221, July 23, 12 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">July 24, noon</hi>]. Reports
                            now current that on September 1st Ottoman Government intends to put into
                            effect 11 percent ad valorem system plus consumption taxes. Refer to
                            Department’s 86, November 15, 6 p.m.<note n="18" xml:id="d866fn18"><ref target="frus1920v03#pg_765"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                        Relations</hi>, 1920, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p.
                                    765</ref>.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>